Drain @black beans{1%can}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the beans, @water{1/4%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{5-10%minutes}. Remove from heat and keep covered until ready to serve.

While beans simmer, wash and dry produce.

Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Drain @mango{4%oz} and place in a #small bowl{}; add @pico de gallo{4%oz}, a pinch of cilantro, and juice from one lime wedge.

Massage @microwaveable jasmine rice{1%pouch} in package to break up grains. Tear off top 2 inches of pouch to vent. Microwave until warmed through, ~{90%seconds}.

> Microwave times may vary. Be careful when handling and opening the microwaved pouch.

Place rice in a #large bowl{} and add lime zest, half the remaining cilantro, juice from one lime wedge, salt, and pepper.

> TIP: For richer-tasting rice, stir in 1-2 TBSP butter.

Divide cilantro-lime rice between shallow bowls and top with beans and mango salsa. Dollop with @guacamole{4%tbsp} and sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Drizzle bowls with as much @hot sauce{1%tsp} as you like and serve with remaining lime wedges.